{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":269417,"duration_api_ms":267996,"num_turns":18,"result":"Based on my thorough investigation of the codebase, here is the planning payload:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"problem_framing\": \"The problem statement requests that stage artifacts (history/artifacts/*.json) record backend_family and model_id from the ResolvedBackendTarget via InvocationEnvelope.metadata. Upon investigation, the codebase ALREADY implements this: RecordProducer::Agent { backend_family, model_id } is populated from envelope.metadata.backend_used.family and envelope.metadata.model_used.model_id at engine.rs:4648-4651. Every artifact creation path sets producer: Some(...) — no code path sets producer: None. Existing artifact JSON files on disk confirm the fields are present (e.g., {\\\"type\\\":\\\"agent\\\",\\\"backend_family\\\":\\\"claude\\\",\\\"model_id\\\":\\\"claude-opus-4-6\\\"}). If the intent is instead to add a separate top-level invocation_metadata field to ArtifactRecord/PayloadRecord (beyond the existing producer field), that would be a new struct addition. The term 'invocation_metadata' does not currently appear anywhere in the src/ directory as a field name.\",\n  \"assumptions_or_open_questions\": [\n    \"The fix appears already implemented: RecordProducer::Agent captures backend_family and model_id from InvocationEnvelope.metadata, and all agent-invocation artifact paths populate this. Is the problem statement outdated, or is there a separate invocation_metadata field intended beyond the existing producer?\",\n    \"If a NEW invocation_metadata field is desired on ArtifactRecord/PayloadRecord (capturing duration, token_counts, session_id, etc. in addition to backend/model), this would require a new serializable struct and changes to both model.rs and engine.rs.\",\n    \"The existing RecordProducer enum has three variants (Agent, LocalValidation, System) — only Agent carries backend_family/model_id. LocalValidation and System records inherently have no backend/model. If the requirement is that ALL records carry this info, the current design is intentionally correct: only agent-produced records have backend/model metadata.\",\n    \"No code path sets producer: None for agent invocations. The Option<RecordProducer> wrapper exists for backward compatibility with older serialized records that predate the producer field (serde default).\"\n  ],\n  \"proposed_work\": [\n    {\n      \"order\": 0,\n      \"summary\": \"Verify existing implementation is correct and complete\",\n      \"details\": \"Confirm all agent invocation code paths in engine.rs, completion.rs, and final_review.rs populate RecordProducer::Agent with backend_family from envelope.metadata.backend_used.family.to_string() and model_id from envelope.metadata.model_used.model_id.clone(). Verified paths: (1) engine.rs:4648-4651 for primary stage records, (2) completion.rs:147-149 for completion panel supporting records, (3) final_review.rs:246-248 for final review supporting records. All paths confirmed correct.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"summary\": \"Confirm artifact JSON output includes producer fields\",\n      \"details\": \"Read existing artifact JSON files in history/artifacts/ to confirm the serialized output includes the producer object with type, backend_family, and model_id. The FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore in src/adapters/fs.rs serializes ArtifactRecord via serde_json, and RecordProducer derives Serialize/Deserialize with a tagged enum (type field). Confirmed: existing artifacts show {\\\"type\\\":\\\"agent\\\",\\\"backend_family\\\":\\\"claude\\\",\\\"model_id\\\":\\\"claude-opus-4-6\\\"}.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"summary\": \"No code changes required — document finding\",\n      \"details\": \"Since the fix is already implemented, no code changes are needed. The backend_family and model_id from InvocationEnvelope.metadata are already propagated into the artifact's producer field via RecordProducer::Agent. If the intent was to add a SEPARATE invocation_metadata field to the record structs, that would require: (1) defining a new InvocationMetadataRecord struct in model.rs with backend_family, model_id, duration_ms, token_counts, and session_id fields; (2) adding an optional invocation_metadata field to ArtifactRecord and PayloadRecord; (3) populating it in engine.rs, completion.rs, and final_review.rs from the InvocationEnvelope. However, this was NOT what the problem described — it specifically asked for backend_family and model_id in the artifact's metadata, which is already present.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"readiness\": {\n    \"ready\": true,\n    \"risks\": [\n      \"The fix described in the problem statement appears to already exist in the codebase. If the intent is different from what's implemented (e.g., adding a separate invocation_metadata field rather than using the existing producer field), the work scope would change significantly.\",\n      \"If the problem was filed against an older version of the code and has since been resolved, proceeding with additional changes could introduce unnecessary complexity or duplication between producer and a new invocation_metadata field.\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f466c4b3-c46a-495a-8ee4-14e78c45066a","total_cost_usd":0.7675814499999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":27951,"cache_read_input_tokens":226073,"output_tokens":7177,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":27951,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":10,"outputTokens":7177,"cacheReadInputTokens":226073,"cacheCreationInputTokens":27951,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.4672052499999999,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":67,"ou